## Purpose

This license allows the source code to be viewed and studied for transparency, security auditing, and educational purposes, while maintaining control over the CommHub brand and official server instances.

## Permissions

You are permitted to:

- Download and use the official CommHub client from GitHub Releases
- View the source code
- Study the implementation for educational purposes
- Audit the code for security vulnerabilities (please report responsibly)
- Reference the code in educational materials with attribution

## Restrictions

You are NOT permitted to:

- Host your own server instance of CommHub (public or private)
- Modify, copy, or distribute the source code
- Create derivative works based on this software
- Use this software for commercial purposes
- Remove or alter copyright notices or this license
- Use the CommHub name or branding for any purpose

## Official Distribution

The official CommHub client is available for download from:

- GitHub Releases: https://github.com/AnthonyRandom/commhub/releases

The official CommHub server is hosted at:

- Official Server: https://commhub-production.up.railway.app

Hosting your own server instance or distributing modified versions of the software is unauthorized and prohibited.

